The paper deals with sublinear and parallel algorithms for approximating constraint satisfaction problems (CSPs), which are a fundamental topic in theoretical computer science. The paper also mentions specific CSPs such as Max-Cut and k-Correlation Clustering, which are commonly studied in the subfields of computational complexity (cs.CC), data structures (cs.DS), discrete mathematics (cs.DM), information theory (cs.IT), and machine learning (cs.LG). Therefore, these are the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories for this paper.
